- I gathered the silk

21:06.900 --> 21:10.200
from my silkworms and I spun it
into thread on my spinning wheel.

21:10.300 --> 21:13.600
- You made it all by yourself?
- Well, the mice and rabbits

21:13.700 --> 21:15.300
did help with the sewing.

21:15.400 --> 21:18.600
- They're good!
- Oh!

21:18.600 --> 21:20.300
Whoa!

21:25.200 --> 21:27.500
Why don't we see about
getting you a car.

21:30.000 --> 21:33.800
- Couldn't she sleep here, Daddy?
- No. That's a big no.

21:40.000 --> 21:43.800
- Are you really a princess?
- Not yet.

21:43.900 --> 21:45.900
But...

21:46.000 --> 21:48.800
...I will be soon.

21:57.700 --> 22:00.800
Wow, Dad.
She's really sleepy.

22:00.900 --> 22:04.400
Oh, no.
That's not acceptable. No.

22:04.500 --> 22:07.500
You're not really gonna
make her go, are you, Daddy?

22:07.500 --> 22:08.800
I want you to go to bed.

22:08.800 --> 22:11.300
But I think she might be
a real princess.

22:11.400 --> 22:16.100
Morgan, just because she has on a funny
dress, doesn't mean she's a princess.

22:16.200 --> 22:19.900
She is a seriously confused woman
who's fallen into our laps.

22:20.000 --> 22:23.300
- So we're not going to let her stay?
- No.

22:23.300 --> 22:25.700
Put on your nightgown
and go to sleep.

22:25.800 --> 22:27.200
Good night, OK?

22:33.000 --> 22:36.800
Hi. I need a car
at 116th and Riverside, please.

22:36.800 --> 22:39.100
<i>- Hold, please.
- Thank you.</i>

22:50.400 --> 22:55.100
<i>Hello, sir.
Destination, please.</i>

22:55.200 --> 22:56.800
<i>Sir?</i>

23:10.900 --> 23:12.300
- Morgan.
- What?

23:12.400 --> 23:14.200
I want you to sleep
in my room tonight.

23:14.200 --> 23:16.200
- Why?
- Just come on.

23:16.300 --> 23:18.100
All right.

23:26.000 --> 23:28.700
Fear not, Giselle!
I will rescue you!

23:28.800 --> 23:33.500
Yeah, but who's
gonna rescue me?

23:34.600 --> 23:37.600
- All right, let's close it up.
- Whoa!

23:39.100 --> 23:41.400
- Hey, buddy! You ain't...
- Silence!

23:41.400 --> 23:42.800
Guys, I got it.

23:42.900 --> 23:45.400
- Your name, peasant! Quickly!
- Arty.

23:45.400 --> 23:47.800
Are you in league with
the wicked old hag who sent

23:47.800 --> 23:50.800
my poor Giselle
to this foul place, Arty?

23:54.900 --> 23:58.700
Is this man party
to this evil plot, chipmunk?

24:09.500 --> 24:12.700
- Uh-oh.
- Aw, poor chipmunk.

24:12.800 --> 24:15.400
Speechless in my presence.

24:15.500 --> 24:17.700
What say you, sir?
Don't try my patience.

24:17.800 --> 24:20.700
- What are you talking about?
- I seek a beautiful girl.

24:20.800 --> 24:22.900
My other half,
my one coquette,

24:23.000 --> 24:24.700
the answer
to my love's duet.

24:24.700 --> 24:26.500
I'd like to
find one of them too.

24:26.600 --> 24:29.800
Then keep a wary eye out, Arty.

24:29.900 --> 24:32.300
- Come along, Pip.
- Are you OK?

24:32.400 --> 24:34.100
Hey!

24:36.000 --> 24:38.400
Hey! Get off the car, you nut!

24:38.400 --> 24:39.800
Did you see that chipmunk?

25:10.800 --> 25:13.800
Oh, my.

25:13.900 --> 25:16.100
This just won't do.

25:33.100 --> 25:34.400
Whoa!

25:50.600 --> 25:54.700
Oh, my goodness.
Are you all right?

25:54.700 --> 25:57.700
Oh.

25:57.800 --> 26:01.100
Hello.

26:02.700 --> 26:04.100
Oh...

26:08.400 --> 26:13.700
Well, it's always nice
to make new friends.

26:13.800 --> 26:17.000
All right, everyone,
let's tidy things up.

26:17.100 --> 26:22.200
<i># Come, my little friends as we all sing
a happy little working song</i>

26:22.200 --> 26:24.400
<i># Merry little voices
Clear and strong</i>

26:24.400 --> 26:27.400
<i># Come and roll your
sleeves up so to speak</i>

26:27.500 --> 26:31.000
<i># And pitch in cleaning
crud up in the kitchen</i>

26:31.100 --> 26:34.200
<i># As we sing along</i>

26:34.300 --> 26:38.900
<i># Trill a cheery tune in the tub
as you scrub a stubborn mildew stain</i>

26:39.000 --> 26:41.400
<i># Pluck a hairball
from the shower drain</i>

26:41.500 --> 26:45.400
<i># To that gay refrain
of a happy working song</i>

26:45.500 --> 26:48.500
<i># We'll keep singing
without fail</i>

26:48.500 --> 26:51.000
<i># Otherwise we'd spoil it</i>

26:51.100 --> 26:56.700
<i># Hosing down the garbage pail
and scrubbing up the toilet</i>

26:56.800 --> 27:00.700
<i># How we all enjoy letting loose with
a little "la da dum dum dum"</i>

27:00.800 --> 27:03.600
<i># While we're emptying the vacu-um</i>

27:03.700 --> 27:04.800
<i># It's such fun</i>

27:04.900 --> 27:08.500
<i>- # To hum a happy working song
- # Ooh</i>

27:08.600 --> 27:11.400
<i># A happy working song</i>

27:11.500 --> 27:16.100
<i># Oh, how strange
a place to be</i>

27:16.200 --> 27:18.600
<i># Till Edward comes for me</i>

27:18.600 --> 27:23.300
<i># My heart is sighing</i>

27:23.400 --> 27:27.100
<i># Still, as long as I am here</i>

27:27.200 --> 27:31.300
<i># I guess a new experience</i>

27:31.300 --> 27:34.100
<i># Could be worth trying</i>

27:34.200 --> 27:37.200
<i># Hey, keep drying</i>

27:37.300 --> 27:39.400
<i># You can do a lot
when you've got such</i>

27:39.500 --> 27:41.900
<i># A happy working tune to hum</i>

27:42.000 --> 27:44.100
<i># While you're sponging up
the soapy scum</i>

27:44.200 --> 27:48.200
<i># We adore each filthy chore
that we determine</i>

27:48.300 --> 27:50.800
<i># So, friends even though
you're vermin</i>

27:50.900 --> 27:56.800
<i># We're a happy working throng</i>

27:56.900 --> 27:59.300
<i># Singing as we fetch
the detergent box</i>

27:59.400 --> 28:02.400
<i># For the smelly shirts
and the stinky socks</i>

28:02.500 --> 28:04.200
<i># Sing along</i>

28:04.300 --> 28:07.100
<i># If you cannot sing
Then hum along</i>

28:07.200 --> 28:12.700
<i># As we're finishing
our happy working song #</i>

28:14.100 --> 28:15.900
Ah.

28:16.000 --> 28:18.500
Wasn't this fun?

28:21.100 --> 28:24.700
- Wake up, wake up!
- What?

28:24.800 --> 28:26.500
- Wake up!
- What is it?

28:26.600 --> 28:29.100
- Come, you have to come see!
- What is it?

28:29.200 --> 28:31.000
I can't tell you.
You have to come see!

28:31.100 --> 28:32.500
What's wrong? Are you OK?

28:32.600 --> 28:37.200
- Yes. What is it, Morgan?
- Look!

28:38.800 --> 28:42.600
Oh, my gosh. Get out! Out!

28:44.700 --> 28:47.500
- What do I do with them?
- Get them outside.

28:47.600 --> 28:49.300
- Get rid of them.
- Put them back?

28:49.300 --> 28:51.500
Put them outside!
Don't put them back.

28:51.500 --> 28:52.800
Open the door!

28:56.000 --> 28:57.900
Good! Watch out!

29:10.500 --> 29:13.100
- Stay there.
- But, Dad.

29:13.200 --> 29:14.900
Shh. Stay there.

29:15.000 --> 29:17.300
- Hello.
- Come in!

29:17.400 --> 29:22.500
- Yeah, can I...
- Oh. Good morning, Robert.

29:22.500 --> 29:26.500
Oh! That's too thoughtful of you.

29:26.600 --> 29:30.200
Thank you! Oh, I hope
you had nice dreams.

29:30.300 --> 29:34.900
- I think I'm still in one.
- This is a magical room.

29:35.000 --> 29:36.800
Where does the water come from?

29:36.800 --> 29:41.400
Uh, well, the water comes
from the pipes.

29:41.500 --> 29:45.900
- And where do the pipes get it?
- Uh, I don't know. From...

29:46.000 --> 29:50.600
...wherever the pipes get it.
- Oh.

29:50.700 --> 29:52.300
It is magical.

29:57.800 --> 30:00.700
- Hey, girlfriend.
- Hi, Nancy.

30:00.800 --> 30:03.400
What do you say,
you ready to kick it?

30:03.500 --> 30:05.200
Kick what?

30:05.300 --> 30:07.100
Why do you still have your PJ's on?

30:07.200 --> 30:09.600
It's been pretty busy around here.

30:12.000 --> 30:14.400
Wow.
It's really neat in here.

30:14.500 --> 30:18.900
- Did you guys get a maid?
- No. Not exactly.

30:18.900 --> 30:21.400
Don't worry.
My friends will do that.

30:21.400 --> 30:26.300
Oh!

30:28.000 --> 30:29.900
- Nancy?
- Oh, hello!

30:30.000 --> 30:32.000
- Who is this?
- This is nothing.

30:32.000 --> 30:33.700
- I'm Giselle!
- This is nobody.

30:33.800 --> 30:36.000
I was on my way to the castle
to get married...

30:36.100 --> 30:37.600
- She's married?
- No, she's not.

30:37.700 --> 30:40.000
- Not yet!
- What does that mean, "yet"?

30:40.100 --> 30:43.300
- She was lost. I was trying to help.
- With finding the shower?

30:43.300 --> 30:45.800
The shower.
The shower is wonderful, Nancy.

30:45.900 --> 30:48.300
- I'm sure it is.
- That's enough. Thank you.

30:48.400 --> 30:51.300
- Calm down. Please, let's talk.
- Talk about what, Robert?

30:51.300 --> 30:53.800
How I never stay the night?
Because we both agreed,

30:53.900 --> 30:56.500
Morgan's here, and you have
to maintain boundaries

30:56.500 --> 30:58.800
and I thought,
"I'm so lucky. He's sensitive!"

30:58.900 --> 31:01.600
I didn't realize you were
worried about crowd control.

31:01.700 --> 31:03.300
- We'll talk.
- Don't bet on it.

31:03.300 --> 31:06.600
What about taking Morgan?
Some grown-up girl-bonding time.

31:06.600 --> 31:10.400
What, so you can have some
grown-up girl-bonding time?

31:10.500 --> 31:13.100
- I don't think so.
- But... just...

31:13.200 --> 31:14.200
Goodbye!

31:16.500 --> 31:18.700
Oh, she is lovely.

31:18.800 --> 31:21.700
Get dressed, please.
For school.

31:21.700 --> 31:24.000
Just... Please.

31:26.500 --> 31:28.400
- Nancy!
- Thirty-eight and Seventh.

31:28.400 --> 31:30.300
Nancy, wait!

31:35.600 --> 31:37.700
- Hello?
- You got to go.

31:37.800 --> 31:41.300
I don't know what your deal is,
if you're waiting for Prince Charming...

31:41.400 --> 31:43.200
- Prince Edward!
- Whatever.

31:43.300 --> 31:45.800
I'll get you to a bus,
a train, a plane, wherever,

31:45.800 --> 31:49.100
and then that's it!
I can't get involved after that.

31:52.900 --> 31:55.800
What is this?

31:55.800 --> 31:58.700
- Where did you get that?
- I made it.

31:58.800 --> 31:59.900
Do you like it?

32:02.100 --> 32:03.700
You're unhappy.

32:03.800 --> 32:05.900
You made a dress out of my curtains?

32:05.900 --> 32:08.700
Oh, you are unhappy.
I am so sorry.

32:08.800 --> 32:11.600
- I'm not unhappy, I'm angry.
- Angry?

32:11.700 --> 32:14.000
It's an unpleasant emotion.
Ever heard of it?

32:14.100 --> 32:17.300
- I have heard of it, but I...
- You have created a completely

32:17.400 --> 32:20.800
unnecessary problem with Nancy
that I now have to resolve.

32:20.900 --> 32:23.200
See, the fact is,
I was just getting ready

32:23.300 --> 32:25.800
to take a very serious step forward.

32:25.900 --> 32:28.000
- A proposal, actually.
- Oh!

32:28.100 --> 32:30.500
Well, now she's got it
in her mind that you and I...

32:30.600 --> 32:34.800
- Kissed?
- Yeah, something like that.

32:34.900 --> 32:38.100
Oh, no.

32:38.100 --> 32:40.700
- You should sing to her!
- Sing to her?

32:40.700 --> 32:43.600
And maybe that would reassure
her of your affections!

32:43.700 --> 32:47.200
You need to rush to her side
and hold her in your arms

32:47.300 --> 32:51.800
and then pour your heart out
in a beautiful ballad.

32:51.900 --> 32:55.400
And then she'll know for sure.

32:57.400 --> 32:59.600
- Why are you staring at me?
- I don't know.

32:59.600 --> 33:02.900
It's like you escaped from
a Hallmark card or something.

33:02.900 --> 33:06.000
Is that a bad thing?

33:06.100 --> 33:09.600
School! We're late!
We've got to run!

33:09.600 --> 33:11.700
Oh!

33:15.800 --> 33:21.700
Oh, wouldn't she just love to come
crawling back here and steal my crown!

33:21.800 --> 33:25.700
Cast me aside like
so much royal rubbish! What?

33:25.700 --> 33:28.900
Perhaps Prince Edward won't find her.

33:29.000 --> 33:31.300
- Perhaps he will!
- Oh! Oh, dear.

33:36.400 --> 33:38.500
Oh...

33:38.600 --> 33:43.800
Oh! I do wish there was someone
who cared enough for me

33:43.900 --> 33:46.700
to go after him.

33:46.800 --> 33:52.500
Oh, a man like that,
strong and brave,

33:52.500 --> 33:56.400
I'd do anything for him.

33:56.500 --> 33:58.700
Never fear, my queen.

33:58.800 --> 34:02.100
I will stop him!

34:10.300 --> 34:12.900
- What now?
- Another one?

34:13.000 --> 34:15.900
Whoa! Get him out of there.
Let's go. Get in there.

34:16.000 --> 34:17.699
Where are these people coming from?

34:17.800 --> 34:19.300
- Come on!
- Upsy-daisy.

34:19.300 --> 34:22.199
Get him up.

34:22.300 --> 34:24.000
- Hey, pal.
- Yow!

34:24.100 --> 34:27.500
Let me guess. You're, uh,
looking for a beautiful girl too.

34:27.500 --> 34:29.300
No.

34:29.400 --> 34:31.699
I'm looking for a prince, actually.

34:33.300 --> 34:36.400
Right.

34:38.900 --> 34:43.000
You've met your match,
you foul bellowing beast!

34:52.800 --> 34:56.800
- Everybody, stay on the bus.
- Giselle? My love?

34:56.900 --> 34:59.300
Drat!

34:59.400 --> 35:02.900
The steel beast is dead, peasants.
I set you all free.

35:03.000 --> 35:05.900
- Move that bus!
- Come on, already!

35:05.900 --> 35:08.900
- Get that bus out of there!
- Are you crazy?

35:09.000 --> 35:12.400
Nobody stabs my bus!
I'll tear you apart!

35:12.400 --> 35:14.100
Do you hear me?

35:14.200 --> 35:16.300
- You get down here!
- If you'll allow me...

35:16.400 --> 35:20.100
- Nathaniel, old friend!
- Sire, may I suggest that you...

35:20.200 --> 35:23.800
You? A friend of his?
Crazy tight-wearing...

35:23.800 --> 35:26.700
Come here and mess up my route?
I'll tear you both apart!

35:26.800 --> 35:30.100
Don't you roll your eyes at me!

35:30.100 --> 35:33.400
A rat!
Get it away from me!

35:33.400 --> 35:36.100
Well, strictly speaking,
he's a chipmunk.

35:36.200 --> 35:40.500
Sire, may I suggest we seek elsewhere

35:40.600 --> 35:42.200
for your bride?

36:01.200 --> 36:03.400
- What are you looking at?
- She's beautiful.

36:03.400 --> 36:05.000
It's just a statue!

36:05.600 --> 36:07.900
Come quickly. Quickly.

36:07.900 --> 36:10.700
Sam? Sam, please don't tell me
Mrs. Banks is already here.

36:10.800 --> 36:12.400
- Mrs. Banks is here.
- Great.

36:12.500 --> 36:14.000
With Mr. Banks and his lawyer.

36:14.100 --> 36:16.100
- Perfect, how long?
- Do you want to know?

36:16.200 --> 36:18.800
No, I don't. I need you to
handle something for me, OK?

36:18.900 --> 36:20.300
- See this girl?
- Who is she?

36:20.400 --> 36:22.800
No idea. I'm pretty sure
she's from out of town.

36:22.800 --> 36:25.000
- What do I do?
- Find out where she's from,

36:25.100 --> 36:27.300
and get her there.
And make sure it's cheap.

36:27.400 --> 36:29.300
If Nancy calls me,
I need to talk to her.

36:29.300 --> 36:31.300
Giselle? Don't drink that, OK?

36:31.300 --> 36:33.700
I have a meeting.
Sam is gonna get you home.

36:33.700 --> 36:35.900
Sam? This is Giselle.
Giselle, this is Sam.

36:35.900 --> 36:37.500
- Yes? Hi.
- Stay out of trouble.

36:40.400 --> 36:43.800
Oh... Oh.

36:43.900 --> 36:47.700
- It's nice to meet you.
- It's nice to meet you too.

36:57.200 --> 36:58.400
Your Majesty.

36:58.400 --> 37:01.200
- Nathaniel!
- Your Majesty?

37:03.100 --> 37:05.100
Nathaniel, here!

37:06.300 --> 37:08.200
Nathaniel!

37:11.400 --> 37:15.600
Finally. Finally.
I'm boiling in here.

37:15.600 --> 37:19.200
- Have you found her yet?
- I'm afraid I haven't, My Lady.

37:19.300 --> 37:22.500
Time is of the essence.

37:22.600 --> 37:25.500
We can't risk my stepson
bringing the girl back.

37:25.600 --> 37:27.600
He shan't, Your Majesty!
I swear it!

37:27.600 --> 37:32.000
No, he shan't. I intend to make
absolutely certain of that.

37:32.000 --> 37:34.800
But, Your Majesty,
how exactly did you...?

37:36.100 --> 37:40.800
...ever end up tasting so...
Mmm... delicious?

37:42.800 --> 37:45.500
Poisoned apples, My Lady.

37:45.500 --> 37:49.100
- You want me to...?
- Don't you see, my darling?

37:49.200 --> 37:54.300
If there's ever going to be
a happily ever after for us...

37:54.400 --> 37:56.700
- Hmm?
- Happily...

37:56.800 --> 38:00.200
...ever after?
Oh, My Lady.

38:00.300 --> 38:02.500
Mmm, yes.
It won't be difficult.

38:02.600 --> 38:06.100
It's just one bite.
That's all it takes.

38:06.200 --> 38:10.300
One small bite to drag her down

38:10.400 --> 38:14.200
into a deep and troubled sleep.

38:14.200 --> 38:16.700
And when the hands
of the clock strike 12,

38:16.800 --> 38:20.200
that precious little pretender
to my throne

38:20.300 --> 38:22.400
will be gone!

38:22.500 --> 38:25.900
It shall be done, My Lady.

38:25.900 --> 38:27.900
- I swear it.
- Yes.

38:28.000 --> 38:31.300
You'll find the girl
at Columbus Circle...

38:32.300 --> 38:33.800
Your Majesty?

38:37.300 --> 38:39.300
Hello.

38:39.300 --> 38:41.200
You little...

38:41.200 --> 38:43.400
Whoa! Hey!

38:54.300 --> 38:56.800
- Pip!
- Sire! Sire, please. I beg of you.

38:56.900 --> 39:00.400
Don't listen to that
insane little vermin.

39:00.500 --> 39:02.400
He's probably eaten some bad nuts.

39:02.500 --> 39:04.500
We should put him down
for his own good.

39:04.600 --> 39:06.300
Nathaniel, please.
Let him speak.

39:06.400 --> 39:09.500
But, sire! No. He's delirious.
He came to tell all sorts of...

39:14.500 --> 39:16.800
Go ahead, Pip.

39:16.800 --> 39:19.500
What is it you want to say?

39:19.600 --> 39:22.200
You watch me. OK?

39:23.400 --> 39:26.200
Nathaniel?

39:26.300 --> 39:28.800
Uh-huh. Nathaniel...

39:28.900 --> 39:32.600
- Nathaniel's glad to have me near.
- No, no, no.

39:32.700 --> 39:35.600
Hmm... Oh!

39:52.300 --> 39:54.200
Oh, oh, oh!
I know this.

39:54.300 --> 39:57.200
- Uh...
- Apple?

39:57.300 --> 39:59.000
No, thank you.

39:59.000 --> 40:00.500
It's good.

40:00.600 --> 40:03.000
Oh, OK.

40:06.800 --> 40:08.300
Ta-da!

40:13.100 --> 40:16.600
You feel you'd die without me here.

40:20.300 --> 40:21.800
Yes. Here we go. Good.

40:21.800 --> 40:24.700
Well, I have to say,
I really think that went well.

40:24.800 --> 40:27.200
There's no reason not
to be reasonable.

40:27.200 --> 40:30.400
Great. We might be in the
neighborhood of a settlement.

40:30.500 --> 40:33.000
Excuse me. I'm gonna
check on your cars for a second.

40:33.100 --> 40:34.600
- Sorry.
- What? What?

40:34.700 --> 40:37.000
She has no driver's license.
No passport.

40:37.100 --> 40:38.900
Can't find this place she comes from.

40:39.000 --> 40:40.100
- What place?
- Andalusia.

40:40.200 --> 40:41.400
- Andalasia.
- Whatever.

40:41.500 --> 40:43.500
I've called every travel agent.

40:43.500 --> 40:45.700
I don't know if it's
a country or a city.

40:45.800 --> 40:48.900
- It can't be a state.
- More like a state of mind.

40:49.000 --> 40:51.900
She told me it's just
beyond the Meadows of Joy

40:51.900 --> 40:55.000
and the Valley of Contentment.
What is that all about?

40:57.800 --> 41:01.600
Oh, my goodness.
Your hair is lovely.

41:01.700 --> 41:04.200
- You're beautiful.
- Well, thank you.

41:04.300 --> 41:07.100
The man who holds your heart
is a lucky fellow indeed.

41:07.200 --> 41:10.000
- You try telling him that.
- I'm certain he already knows.

41:10.100 --> 41:13.700
- Excuse me?
- Are you him?

41:13.800 --> 41:17.900
You are very lucky. Just look
at the way her eyes sparkle.

41:17.900 --> 41:20.900
- It's no wonder you're in love.
- I got it!

41:21.000 --> 41:24.200
Excuse me. I'm sorry.
Giselle? Please?

41:24.300 --> 41:27.300
It's not like that, all right?
They're not together anymore.

41:27.400 --> 41:29.800
- I don't understand.
- They're getting a divorce.

41:29.900 --> 41:32.700
- Separating from each other.
- Separating?

41:32.700 --> 41:34.400
- Yeah.
- For how long?

41:34.500 --> 41:37.600
- Forever.
- Forever and ever?

41:37.700 --> 41:40.500
Shh. Yes.

41:40.600 --> 41:43.200
- Oh, no.
- What are you doing?

41:43.300 --> 41:45.400
- Don't cry.
- Are you crying?

41:45.500 --> 41:47.400
- She's not.
- I'm sorry. I can't help it.

41:47.500 --> 41:50.200
- Is she actually crying?
- It's just so sad.

41:50.300 --> 41:52.700
What kind of an operation
are you running here?

41:52.800 --> 41:54.400
This is so unprofessional.

41:54.400 --> 41:57.000
Good morning, Phoebe.
How are you? It's good to...

41:57.100 --> 41:59.500
If you guys
are trying to manipulate us,

41:59.600 --> 42:02.300
you can throw this whole deal out.

42:04.300 --> 42:06.400
What is going on here?
Who's she?

42:06.500 --> 42:09.000
Uh, a friend. No, she's
an acquaintance, actually.

42:09.100 --> 42:12.300
You begged me to put you on the case,
and this is what I get for it?

42:12.300 --> 42:14.500
I walk in here
and find everybody upset?

42:14.600 --> 42:16.800
<i>And some girl is crying
like we're on Oprah.</i>

42:16.900 --> 42:20.100
I'll take care of it.
Carl, it's gonna be fine.

42:20.200 --> 42:22.600
- What is wrong with you?
- Me?

42:22.700 --> 42:25.300
<i>Yes, you. This whole Kumbaya,
Up With People routine.</i>

42:25.400 --> 42:28.300
- Those people are in real pain.
- Of course they're in pain.

42:28.300 --> 42:29.700
They're separated forever.

42:29.800 --> 42:31.900
Married one day
and the next they're not.

42:31.900 --> 42:34.500
- What sort of awful place is this?
- It's reality.

42:34.500 --> 42:36.800
Well, I think I'd prefer to be
in Andalasia.

42:36.900 --> 42:39.700
- I think I'd prefer that too.
- Get in, please.

42:41.700 --> 42:46.700
I wonder if we might cover
more ground separately, sire.

42:46.800 --> 42:50.700
Uh, you by yourself,
and me with it.

42:50.800 --> 42:53.500
An inspired plan, Nathaniel.

42:53.600 --> 42:55.800
Where do you suppose I should look?

43:07.000 --> 43:09.200
Look, sire! Over there!

43:09.300 --> 43:10.700
Ah! Giselle!

43:10.800 --> 43:14.700
Run to her, sire! Hurry!
Not a moment to lose!

43:14.800 --> 43:18.000
- Giselle!
- I try to do the right thing.

43:18.000 --> 43:19.600
Oh, you've been very nice to me.

43:19.700 --> 43:23.700
Severely punished for it.
OK, look, Giselle?

43:23.800 --> 43:25.900
- I can't help you anymore. OK?
- What?

43:26.000 --> 43:29.600
Here's some money. I want you
to take it. Call your prince.

43:29.700 --> 43:31.600
Have him pick you up,
bring his horse.

43:31.600 --> 43:34.500
Because I honestly,
I just can't handle it.

43:34.500 --> 43:37.900
- Robert?
- Just go.

43:38.000 --> 43:40.300
I'm so sorry.

43:40.400 --> 43:43.200
You have been a very kind friend
to me when I had none.

43:43.300 --> 43:47.700
