- Mmm!

45:46.900 --> 45:49.900
- Let me put that out for you.
- What about you?

45:50.000 --> 45:54.300
- How long have you known your Nancy?
- Uh, it's five years.

45:54.400 --> 45:57.100
- And you haven't proposed?
- Well, no. I...

45:57.200 --> 45:58.700
Well, no wonder she's angry.

45:58.800 --> 46:01.000
Hello, nice lady.

46:01.100 --> 46:05.000
You want juicy,
sweet caramel apple, maybe?

46:05.000 --> 46:06.200
Mm.

46:06.200 --> 46:08.900
No charge for the beautiful
young woman.

46:08.900 --> 46:10.800
- Oh, really. It's free?
- Of course!

46:10.900 --> 46:13.600
Today is free caramel apple day.

46:13.700 --> 46:18.000
Tomorrow is free beef... jerky.

46:18.100 --> 46:20.500
Thank you very much, kind sir.

46:20.600 --> 46:24.800
You're welcome, miss.

46:24.900 --> 46:26.600
You...

46:30.700 --> 46:32.800
Shut up.

46:32.900 --> 46:36.100
Most normal people get to know
each other before they get married.

46:36.200 --> 46:38.400
They date.

46:38.400 --> 46:40.600
- Date?
- Yeah. You know, date.

46:40.700 --> 46:43.800
You go someplace special.
You know, like a restaurant,

46:43.900 --> 46:47.900
or a movie, a museum. Or you
just hang out and you talk.

46:48.000 --> 46:51.200
- What do you talk about?
- About each other.

46:51.200 --> 46:53.700
About yourself.
About your interests.

46:53.800 --> 46:56.000
Your likes, your dislikes.
You talk!

46:56.100 --> 46:58.800
You have such strange
ideas about love.

46:58.800 --> 47:02.500
Maybe we should do what you would do.
You meet, have lunch, and get married.

47:02.600 --> 47:04.600
Oh! You forgot
about happily ever after.

47:04.700 --> 47:07.000
Forget "happily ever after."
It doesn't exist.

47:07.100 --> 47:09.400
Well, of course it does.
Oh!

47:09.400 --> 47:11.400
Oh!

47:11.500 --> 47:14.500
I hate to disagree,
but marriages are a success

