57:42.825 --> 57:45.385
- This is a date.
- Yeah.

57:45.461 --> 57:49.022
No! No! No, no. We're just...

57:49.098 --> 57:51.089
We're just friends.

57:51.166 --> 57:55.102
Besides, people don't usually
bring their children on dates.

57:56.071 --> 57:57.538
That's too bad.

57:57.606 --> 58:01.235
Morgan's a lovely girl.
She's very kind and very sweet.

58:01.310 --> 58:03.278
Yeah. She's great.

58:05.848 --> 58:10.080
- What?
- Does she miss her terribly?

58:10.152 --> 58:11.949
- Miss who?
- Her mother.

58:12.021 --> 58:13.386
Um...

58:14.623 --> 58:16.648
- Well, we just...
- What?

58:19.128 --> 58:21.153
- We don't talk about it.
- Oh.

58:21.230 --> 58:23.391
I'm very sorry.
I didn't mean to pry.

58:23.465 --> 58:25.626
No, no. It's OK.
It's just...

58:27.369 --> 58:31.829
I don't talk about it...
to Morgan or to anybody.

58:31.907 --> 58:35.308
- Because it was very sad?
- Not at first.

58:35.377 --> 58:39.108
- You were in love.
- Yeah.

58:39.181 --> 58:41.411
Yeah.

58:41.483 --> 58:44.475
- That was the problem.
- How could that be a problem?

58:44.553 --> 58:48.216
Because love... The lovey-dovey
version that you talk about?

58:48.290 --> 58:50.383
It's fantasy.

58:50.459 --> 58:52.893
And one day,
you have to wake up and...

58:54.330 --> 58:57.925
...you're in the real world.
- What made you wake up?

58:59.702 --> 59:01.397
Well...

59:04.807 --> 59:06.365
...she left.

59:08.811 --> 59:12.372
- I'm so sorry for you both.
